            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Can I finance a used truck that is 10+ years old?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Yes, though options are more limited. Some lenders have maximum age restrictions (for example, the truck must be no more than 15 or 20 years old at the end of the loan term). Specialist commercial vehicle lenders are more flexible with age limits than mainstream banks. Rates will be higher for older trucks. Having a strong business profile and a deposit can help secure finance for older vehicles.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Do I need a truck licence to get truck finance?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Lenders do not typically check your licence class as part of the finance approval. However, operating a truck without the appropriate licence is illegal. You need an LR (Light Rigid) licence for trucks over 4.5t GVM, MR (Medium Rigid) for two-axle trucks over 8t, HR (Heavy Rigid) for three or more axles, and HC/MC for prime movers and multi-combination vehicles.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Can I finance a truck and trailer together?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Yes. Many lenders will finance a truck and trailer as a combined package under one loan. This can simplify your finance and may achieve a better rate than financing them separately. Alternatively, they can be financed as separate assets with individual loans if you prefer flexibility to change trailers.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">What about truck finance for new operators?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">If you are new to the trucking industry, finance options exist but are more limited. Lenders like to see relevant industry experience (even if your ABN is new), a clean personal credit history, a deposit of 10-20%, and a strong business plan or existing contracts. Some specialist lenders have programs specifically for new operators. Nik Finance can identify the right lender for your situation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
